The Iraq-Oncology Teaching Hospital/National Center for Cancer Diseases (IQ-OTH/NCCD) lung cancer dataset was collected in the specialist hospitals over a period of three months in fall 2019.¶

Through Data Augmentation I have increased the size of the Image data by 2x times for model to train.

Convert Image to Array¶

In [2]:
#Path of the folders with training images
Bengin="data/The IQ-OTHNCCD lung cancer dataset/Bengin cases"
Malignant="data/The IQ-OTHNCCD lung cancer dataset/Malignant cases"
Normal="data/The IQ-OTHNCCD lung cancer dataset/Normal cases"
In [3]:
img_array=[]
labels=[]
In [4]:
#Convert image to array with labels
#Bengin Cases
for filename in os.listdir(Bengin):
    file_path=os.path.join(Bengin,filename)
    if os.path.isfile(file_path):
        img = image.load_img(file_path, target_size=(320, 320))
        array = image.img_to_array(img)
        img_array.append(array)
        labels.append(1)

#Malignant Cases
for filename in os.listdir(Malignant):
    file_path=os.path.join(Malignant,filename)
    if os.path.isfile(file_path):
        img = image.load_img(file_path, target_size=(320, 320))
        array = image.img_to_array(img)
        img_array.append(array)
        labels.append(2)
        
#Normal Cases
for filename in os.listdir(Normal):
    file_path=os.path.join(Normal,filename)
    if os.path.isfile(file_path):
        img = image.load_img(file_path, target_size=(320, 320))
        array = image.img_to_array(img)
        img_array.append(array)
        labels.append(0)
In [5]:
x=np.array(img_array)
y=np.array(labels)

# NORMALIZE
x=x/255.0

Create Model¶

In [21]:
model = keras.Sequential([
    keras.layers.Conv2D(32, (3, 3), activation="relu", input_shape=(320, 320, 3)),
    keras.layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),
    keras.layers.Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation="relu"),
    keras.layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),
    keras.layers.Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation="relu"),
    keras.layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),
    keras.layers.Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation="relu"),
    keras.layers.Flatten(),
    keras.layers.Dense(64, activation="relu"),
    keras.layers.Dense(128, activation="relu"),
    keras.layers.Dense(64, activation="relu"),
    keras.layers.Dense(3, activation="softmax"),
])

In [26]:
# ADD test path
test_path = 'data/Test cases/' 
testing_img = []

for filename in os.listdir(test_path):
    file_path = os.path.join(test_path, filename)
    if os.path.isfile(file_path):
        img = image.load_img(file_path, target_size=(320, 320))
        array = image.img_to_array(img)
        testing_img.append(array)

testing_img = np.array(testing_img)
# Normalize
testing_img = testing_img / 255.0

predictions = model.predict(testing_img)
predicted_labels = np.argmax(predictions, axis=1)

class_names = {0: 'Normal', 1: 'Bengin', 2: 'Malignant'}
predicted_classes = [class_names[label] for label in predicted_labels]
